**Professional Profile**
Mai Nhat Duy is a final-year Computer Science student with emerging experience in the information technology sector, particularly within AI and NLP research. As a Research Assistant at TDTU NLP-KD Lab, Mai has actively contributed to exploring and applying AI and Natural Language Processing (NLP) technologies to real-world problems. This role provided practical experience in training language models, including crucial data collection and processing, even with limited hardware resources. This foundational experience highlights a strong interest and practical engagement in cutting-edge AI research and development.

**Core Skills & Technology**
Proficient in key technologies and methodologies including Artificial Intelligence (AI), Natural Language Processing (NLP), and Large Language Models (LLM). Technical skills encompass Python, PyTorch, Transformer, LangChain, Model Training, Data Collection, and Data Preprocessing.

**Education & Certifications**
Mai is currently a final-year Computer Science student at Ton Duc Thang University. Further demonstrating professional aptitude, Mai holds an Aptis ESOL certification at CEFR Level B2, indicating strong English language proficiency.